---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How I Engage — Wychwood Partners"
  description="Fractional COO and Operating Partner support focused on capital discipline, integration, and scalable operating systems."
>
  <main class="shell section">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h1>Operating Partner, Fractional COO</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
        I work with private equity investors, boards, and founders when the business needs tighter performance control —
        clearer numbers, faster decisions, and an operating rhythm that holds.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
        The through-line is capital discipline: margin protection, liquidity awareness, and board-ready visibility — without adding bureaucracy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 grid gap-12">
      <section class="card p-8">
        <h2>Post-Investment Stabilization (0–180 Days)</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          <li>Rapid diagnostic to find where variance is coming from (margin, conversion, cost, throughput).</li>
          <li>Cost-base and operating reset that protects capacity while stopping the bleed.</li>
          <li>13-week cash visibility so liquidity stops being a surprise.</li>
          <li>Scenario plan with explicit triggers for action (not a spreadsheet exercise).</li>
          <li>100-day plan with owners, milestones, and board-level reporting.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          In practice, this is about restoring control quickly: fewer meetings, clearer thresholds, and decisions that close.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card p-8">
        <h2>Scale & Replication</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          <li>Multi-site operating model so performance is consistent across locations and leaders.</li>
          <li>International supply chain buildout and market-entry mechanics when expansion goes global.</li>
          <li>Unit economics visibility that ties growth decisions to margin and working capital.</li>
          <li>Forecasting and capital planning that supports board conversations and (when relevant) IPO readiness.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          Growth is gated by operating readiness. The goal is scale that stays profitable.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card p-8">
        <h2>Post-Merger Integration Leadership</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          <li>Integration office setup (IMO) with clear decision rights and a single operating plan.</li>
          <li>KPI and reporting alignment so leadership is steering one business, not two.</li>
          <li>Synergy tracking that is measurable, owned, and reviewed on a fixed cadence.</li>
          <li>Leadership and culture decisions handled quickly when ambiguity is slowing execution.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          Acquisitions create complexity. The job is to convert that complexity into enterprise value.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card p-8">
        <h2>Founder-to-Scale Partnership</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          <li>Turn founder intent into a practical operating model with real ownership and thresholds.</li>
          <li>Install a weekly cadence where priorities don’t drift and decisions don’t float.</li>
          <li>Build capital-efficient growth mechanics (inventory, staffing, coverage, unit economics).</li>
          <li>Prepare the business for institutional capital — venture, private equity, or public markets.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          I’m hands-on with founders, but I’m always investor-aligned: the numbers have to hold.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card-muted p-8">
        <h2>Engagement Models</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-[rgb(var(--text-muted))]">
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))]">Fractional COO:</span>
            weekly cadence, decision support, and operator ownership of the execution system.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))]">Interim operator:</span>
            time-bound leadership (30–180 days) to stabilize, integrate, or scale.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))]">Operating Partner support:</span>
            diligence, 100-day plan, and board-ready reporting through the hold period.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] bg-[rgb(var(--brand-anchor))] px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-white transition hover:opacity-95"
          >
            Book a call
          </a>
          <a
            href="/case-studies"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] border border-[rgb(var(--border))] bg-[rgb(var(--surface-elevated))] px-5 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[rgb(var(--text))] transition hover:bg-[rgb(var(--surface-subtle))]"
          >
            View case studies
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
